Oluwatosin Omojuyigbe The Lagos State Government on Wednesday said its N1.15trn 2021 budget aimed at consolidating the gains of democracy would prioritise employment generation, food security and youth empowerment. The state Commissioner for Budget and Economic Planning, Sam Egube, stated this to the members of the Implementation Monitoring Committee of the National Economic Council during a routine check of the state governmentâ€™s projects. A statement on Wednesday said Egube noted that 2021 would witness the inauguration of completed projects and development of new infrastructure. The commissioner added that the state government was adopting geospatial data system to enhance quality governance and interact practically with stakeholders in all sectors in the state to provide adequate information in the area of business development, health, agriculture, food security, education and transportation, among other services. The Minister of State for Budget and National Planning, Clem Agba, who led the delegation to the state, was quoted to have said that the Federal Government was developing an app to monitor projects to bridge the trust gap between government and citizens. Copyright PUNCH.
